<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,152,1522]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,339,1383,1409]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is dedicated to Dr. Oleksiy Bidzilya, who kindly supported us to solve many difficult taxonomical problems concernig the Eastern Palearctic fauna of 
<taxonomicName box="[1008,1152,1421,1447]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Gelechiidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,152,1522]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis box="[198,289,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Remark</emphasis>
. The species is not mentioned in a review of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[941,1027,1459,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Athrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[941,1027,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Athrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Palaearctic region (Bidzilya 
<number box="[151,215,1496,1522]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="2005.0">2005</number>
).
</paragraph>
